# Main Project Rules

## General Principles

- Use TypeScript with explicit types. Avoid implicit `any`.
- Prefer function declarations over arrow functions.
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling. No custom CSS unless absolutely necessary.
- Follow modern React patterns with Next.js 15 App Router.
- Write focused, composable components and utilities.

## Code Style

### Function Declarations

```typescript
// ✅ Preferred
function MyComponent() {
  return <div>Hello</div>
}

// ❌ Avoid
const MyComponent = () => {
  return <div>Hello</div>
}
```

### TypeScript

```typescript
// ✅ Explicit types
function processUser(user: User): ProcessedUser {
  return { ...user, processed: true };
}

// ❌ Avoid implicit any
function processUser(user) {
  return { ...user, processed: true };
}
```

### Styling

```typescript
// ✅ Tailwind classes
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm">
  <h1 className="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Title</h1>
</div>

// ❌ Custom CSS
<div className="custom-container">
  <h1 className="custom-title">Title</h1>
</div>
```

## File Organization

- Components go in `src/components/`
- Pages go in `src/app/`
- Utilities go in `src/lib/`
- Types go in `src/types/`
- Validations go in `src/validations/`
- Tests live alongside the code they test (e.g., `src/components/__tests__/`)

## Testing Strategy

- Use Jest for unit tests
- Use Cypress for E2E tests
- Use React Testing Library for component tests
- Tests should be in the same directory as the code they test
- Use descriptive test names that explain the behavior

## Database

- Use Prisma for database operations
- Define schemas in `prisma/schema.prisma`
- Use migrations for schema changes
- Keep models focused and well-typed

## Forms & Validation

- Use React Hook Form for form state
- Use Zod for validation schemas
- Create reusable form components
- Validate on both client and server side

